cs.AR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes a hardware architecture named Efficient Speech Recognition Engine (ESE) that works directly on the compressed model. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it discusses Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) models and their use in speech recognition. Additionally, it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) because speech recognition is a subfield of computer vision, and cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it proposes a load-balance-aware pruning method and a scheduler for parallel processing.
